Sri Lankan-origin doctor arrested in Canada for possessing child sexual abuse material]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132555870.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/sri-lankan-origin-doctor-arrested-in-canada-for-possessing-child-sexual-abuse-material/articleshow/132555870.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/sri-lankan-origin-doctor-arrested-in-canada-for-possessing-child-sexual-abuse-material/articleshow/132555870.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T15:38:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132556194,imgsize-373916.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meet Hedy Lamarr: Hollywood icon whose invention laid the foundation for modern Wi-Fi]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132555259.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Hedy Lamarr, widely known for her illustrious acting career, also made significant strides in technology by inventing a communication system that used frequency hopping to encrypt radio signals in wartime. Her pioneering work paved the way for the development of contemporary innovations such as Wi-Fi and Bluetooth. Although her achievements were initially overlooked, she has since been recognized as a trailblazer in both the entertainment and tech industries.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-hedy-lamarr-most-beautiful-woman-in-the-world-who-married-an-arms-dealer-became-a-hollywood-icon-and-invented-a-radio-signalling-system-during-world-war-ii-becoming-the-mother-of-wi-fi/articleshow/132555259.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-hedy-lamarr-most-beautiful-woman-in-the-world-who-married-an-arms-dealer-became-a-hollywood-icon-and-invented-a-radio-signalling-system-during-world-war-ii-becoming-the-mother-of-wi-fi/articleshow/132555259.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T15:58:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132555300,imgsize-162214.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Arizona teen helps elderly woman with dementia in 103F heat, officials warn of confusion as a sign of heatstroke]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132555101.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Royal Cothrun, a fourteen-year-old boy, demonstrated extraordinary courage during a perilous heatwave by rescuing an elderly woman wandering aimlessly. With a swift instinct, he provided shade and facilitated her communication with her son, actions that were potentially lifesaving. The Arizona fire department is set to commend him for his heroic efforts, highlighting the critical risks associated with severe summer heat.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-14-year-old-arizona-boy-helped-save-an-elderly-woman-with-dementia-who-was-wandering-in-103f-heat-as-officials-warn-sudden-confusion-can-be-a-sign-of-heatstroke/articleshow/132555101.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-14-year-old-arizona-boy-helped-save-an-elderly-woman-with-dementia-who-was-wandering-in-103f-heat-as-officials-warn-sudden-confusion-can-be-a-sign-of-heatstroke/articleshow/132555101.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T14:37:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132555121,imgsize-115820.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists are planning to install an 80km underwater curtain to stop an Antarctic glavier from melting, here's why]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132554987.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In an exciting scientific endeavor, researchers are exploring the idea of constructing a massive underwater curtain to defend Thwaites Glacier against warm ocean currents. This strategic barrier is intended to redirect these warmer waters, aiming to curb the glacier's swift melting. A recent expedition gathered vital information from the Amundsen Sea to determine the project's feasibility, while additional studies in Svalbard focus on understanding the environmental ramifications of the barrier.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/warm-ocean-water-is-melting-a-giant-antarctic-glacier-from-below-scientists-want-to-stop-it-with-an-80km-underwater-curtain/articleshow/132554987.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/warm-ocean-water-is-melting-a-giant-antarctic-glacier-from-below-scientists-want-to-stop-it-with-an-80km-underwater-curtain/articleshow/132554987.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T14:28:30+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132555042,imgsize-107084.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[The secret lives of whale sharks finally unveiled!]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132555028.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[New findings have shown that whale sharks are capable of diving deeper than seventy meters when hunting for food. These majestic giants use a variety of feeding strategies, moving beyond just grazing at the surface. Remarkable underwater footage captured via cameras attached to the sharks highlights their feeding dynamics, showcasing low-energy grazing alongside energetic krill chases. This study enhances our grasp of their intricate foraging patterns.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-attach-cameras-to-whale-sharks-capturing-how-the-worlds-biggest-fish-hunts-like-never-before/articleshow/132555028.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-attach-cameras-to-whale-sharks-capturing-how-the-worlds-biggest-fish-hunts-like-never-before/articleshow/132555028.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T14:38:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132555128,imgsize-103664.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Rampage Jackson vs Sweatergxd controversy explained after MMA legend punches Kick streamer live]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132554521.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A party encounter between MMA legend Rampage Jackson and Kick streamer Sweatergxd turned physical after the streamer repeatedly touched Jackson inappropriately, including his groin area. After issuing several verbal warnings and telling him not to touch him again, Jackson threw a punch before leaving the scene, with the incident now circulating widely online.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/rampage-jackson-vs-sweatergxd-controversy-explained-after-mma-legend-punches-kick-streamer-in-the-face/articleshow/132554521.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/rampage-jackson-vs-sweatergxd-controversy-explained-after-mma-legend-punches-kick-streamer-in-the-face/articleshow/132554521.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T14:23:3